    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5253" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρας</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέραος</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέραι</span>
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρᾳ</span>), pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρᾱ</span> (but shortened before a vowel), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεράων</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρασι,
            κεράεσσι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">horn;</span> bows were made of horn,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 4.109</span></i> ff., <i><span class="en">Od. 21.395</span></i>; hence said for ‘bow,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 11.385</span></i>; a sheath of horn was used to
          encase a fishing-line, to prevent the hook from being bitten off,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 24.81</span></i>; with a play upon the word
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κραίνω</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 19.566</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
